a year of motherhood. even though I never share mommy stuff on here, today I’m in the mood to do so. giving birth was my biggest fear since I was little, and accomplishing that was quite an achievement for me (especially after such a difficult pregnancy).I feel as though it changed me as a person entirely. it felt like a rebirth. everything is different. my anxiety surrounding my body is completely gone, (I’ve always been the biggest hypochondriac) it’s quite the phenomenon. - this fearlessness & almost aggressiveness that ignited within me is all… nature. to be a mother, a protector. it’s such a profound experience. I’ve spent this last year loving this tiny human I created so deeply, I didn’t think was possible (besides @losrose__ ). I spent an entire year exclusively breastfeeding (which was INTENSE while traveling & working) and I’m still going!!! the lack of sleep at times was ghastly. but the way I feel about my son.. family, my husband & my accomplishments this last year, are the complete opposite. mothers are the backbone of our societies and homes. shoutout to the men, MY MAN, that do their part, without needing to be asked to do so.. the men who care for their children the same way mothers do.. is a rare find. anyway, if you’re a mother, give yourself a fkn HUG. If you have a mother, HUG HER ❤️‍🔥 cheers to me forever balancing motherhood, the career that I love so much, my strong marriage & my amazing friends. I love you all.
